channel.title: Realm Onwards - The RSPS for Newcomers - PI Version - NEW NAME
channel.description:
[center] [size=36pt] Realm Onwards The RSPS for Newcomers The PI Version
[img]http://img17.imageshack.us/img17/4186/59164447.png[/img] [/size][/center]
I am deciding to make a new project. I named it "Realm Onwards". I believe that this will work through, and make a nice base for new coders. This will have different versions, though it's not like v1 and v2, it's like PI version and Delta version. You better see this when it's done :p.
[center] [img]http://img197.imageshack.us/img197/367/fun4.png[/img][/center]
This is going to be for all the newcomers. Don't some of the "Server Help" guys get annoyed? This was designed to make less of those common sense things. Unlike Blankscape or "Blank Source + Client" this works upon all sources, ranging from 317 delta to those of 639.
[center] [img]http://img31.imageshack.us/img31/7006/fun2.png[/img][/center] As I said before, this was partly designed to keep common sense topic out. My main point is to help the community. I have always had a feeling in my life to help all, not leave anyone behind. If I do, I'll get really regretful mode. If I don't complete or atleast make 1 version of "Realm Onwards" then consider myself not promising to a community. This goal is: "Learning's Fun!" I would like to make a fun, creative, and most of all learning server for newcomers
[center] [img]http://img855.imageshack.us/img855/2920/fun3z.png[/img] [img]http://www.upload.ee/image/1932577/clip0004.gif[/img][/center]
This server provides:
Complete Started Not Started
[ul][li]The Incredible Learning Center[/li] [li]Far-range bows[/li] [li]Far-range magic[/li] [li]A Reasonable Starter[/li] [li]New hitmarks (If possible)[/li] [li]Critical Hits[/li] [li]Blocking spammers[/li] [li]Ability to press enter to login instead of clicking login[/li] [li]Vengeance on NPC[/li] [li]New curses[/li] [li]Extreme Potions[/li] [li]A life-like rsps dialogue such as "How are you doing?" from Man[/li] [li]Full doors[/li] [li]Pvp Armors (All effects and specials)[/li] [li]Chaotic weapons (Works just like RS)[/li] [li]Tormented Demons - Correct Emotes/GFX[/li] [li]Corperal Beast - Correct Emotes/GFX drops spirit shields/sigils[/li] [li]Perfect Staff of Light[/li] [li]Clipped Following[/li] [li]Combat following[/li] [li]604 Gameplay[/li] [li]RS Firecape[/li] [li]100% Skillcape Emotes[/li] [li]100% Pking[/li] [li]100% Bridding/Item Switching[/li] [li]Barrows and effects[/li] [li]Pk points and EP System[/li] [li]Perfect Xp rates[/li] [li]100% Dragon claws with perfected emote[/li] [li]100% All godsword specials[/li] [li]NO DUPES[/li] [li]THERE IS NO "DONATOR ONLY" ITEMS! You can add it (tutorial in it). Anyone can use anything if they have the proper requirements![/li] [li]Shops are located in Varrock[/li] [li]All spirit shields and their effects (Divine - Deducts 30% damage, Elysian - 70% chance to deduct, Arcane - +20 Magic Attack Bonus, and Spectral - +30 magic defence bonus)[/li] [li]A perfect economy server[/li] [li]Slayer helmet gives 50% extra exp when doing slayer[/li] [li]Lock exp[/li] [li]Every single skill works[/li] [li]Saradomin Sword Spec[/li][/ul]
[center] [img]http://img860.imageshack.us/img860/5958/fun1d.png[/img] [url=http://picasion.com/][img]http://i.picasion.com/pic48/b4296297c383757f4c6bd6b78d5fcbc8.gif[/img][/url][/center]
[b]I Am Sanity:[/b] For PI [b]Moparscape:[/b] Awesome forums! [b]Arham 4:[/b] Adding things to server [b]Some tutorials:[/b] For providing things to help this. [b]RuneLive:[/b] An amazing base for source and client.
If you like this, then you'll probably like these:
[ul][li][url=https://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,530273.0.html]A nice clean folder fit for making RSPS work faster - Realm Onwards Program[/url][/li] [li][url=https://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,529971.0.html][PI]How to make a .ini file for your server - Briefly Explained![/url][/li] [li][url=https://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,530221.0.html]Mini-Tutorials and List folder - Part of the: Realm Onwards Program - V2 OUT[/url][/li][/ul]
